Joe Frisco https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Frisco 0 Joe Frisco (born Louis Wilson Joseph; November 4, 1889 – February 12, 1958) was an American vaudeville performer who first made his name on stage as a jazz dancer, but later incorporated his stuttering voice to his act and became a popular comedian.
